1
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:49,480
Traces of an anesthetic were detected
in the victim's blood.

2
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:52,600
A distinct injection mark on the neck.

3
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:55,240
Multiple signs of struggle on the limbs.

4
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:57,280
The surface of the body
shows a cherry-red color.

5
00:01:57,360 --> 00:01:59,000
That's the typical sign of death
caused by hypothermia.

6
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:04,320
In other words,
Mei got into a fight with someone.

7
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:07,120
During the struggle,
he was injected with an anesthetic

8
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:08,960
before being stuffed into the freezer.

9
00:02:10,320 --> 00:02:11,480
Time of death?

10
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:12,560
Around four weeks ago.

11
00:02:12,640 --> 00:02:14,040
Four weeks ago?

12
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:16,640
Only one student
went missing at that time.

13
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:19,880
The other four students
weren't taken by Mei.

14
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:24,200
Could he have had an accomplice?

15
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:26,760
Maybe they argued over something,

16
00:02:26,840 --> 00:02:28,320
then the accomplice killed him

17
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:30,040
and kept using the old method
to continue the crimes.

18
00:02:34,760 --> 00:02:39,040
JUNE 10TH, 2015, REPORT FILED

19
00:02:40,720 --> 00:02:41,960
At this stage of the case,

20
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:44,080
there's a strong chance Mei's accomplice

21
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:45,880
has taken the four children
out of Weiyang.

22
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:49,080
And right now, we still have no new leads.

23
00:02:51,040 --> 00:02:53,320
Tomorrow is the last day
of the seven-day deadline.

24
00:02:53,920 --> 00:02:57,920
How about we ask Director Zou
for two more days?

25
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:07,200
I made a promise.

26
00:03:08,040 --> 00:03:08,960
Don't be discouraged.

27
00:03:10,040 --> 00:03:11,280
Even if we miss the deadline,

28
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,760
I'll take responsibility.

29
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:16,080
You all keep looking for the children.
Don't stop until they're found.

30
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:28,760
If only we had listened to Xiaohe earlier

31
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:30,600
and focused all our manpower
on investigating Yuanlongli,

32
00:03:30,680 --> 00:03:33,120
maybe there would be no regrets.

33
00:03:45,760 --> 00:03:48,920
There's no sign at all
of Mei's accomplice or the four children.

34
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:51,720
If we keep digging around this place,
does it still mean anything?

35
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:56,560
No. 1316 shows no signs
of anyone living there after Mei died.

36
00:03:56,640 --> 00:03:58,320
But the kidnappings kept happening,

37
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:00,200
using the same old method.

38
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:01,840
What does that tell us?

39
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:07,960
Hey, you.

40
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:09,360
What is that?

41
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:13,160
A strategic meeting needs to come up
with a real-time battle plan or something.

42
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:15,040
Go do your thing. Stay out of the way.

43
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:16,959
Alright.

44
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:24,040
Where was I?

45
00:04:24,960 --> 00:04:26,080
What does that tell us?

46
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:31,160
To snatch children away
from a crowded and exposed place

47
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:35,000
suggests a hidden route.

48
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:40,360
A hidden route?

49
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:43,600
Captain Qu has turned
this place upside down.

50
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:45,360
We're not checking
the internet café today.

51
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:47,320
We're checking the ways out of it.

52
00:04:48,440 --> 00:04:51,520
First, check the B1 route.

53
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:54,440
Second, check the garage exit route.

54
00:04:54,960 --> 00:04:56,840
Same method as before. Block both ends.

55
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:04,600
You're not eating your instant noodles?

56
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:13,840
NEW YORK BLOCK

57
00:05:16,080 --> 00:05:17,880
NEED GLASSES? FIND US AT OPTICAL
INSTALLMENT PLANS, CREDIT CARDS

58
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:24,600
- Are you a police officer?
- Yes.

59
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:26,760
Last week, I told you
my platform truck was stolen.

60
00:05:27,520 --> 00:05:29,320
Can you do something about it?

61
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:30,960
When are you sending someone
to look into it?

62
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:34,880
Mister, we're working on a case.
I'll help you find it once we're done.

63
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:37,520
What did the platform truck look like?

64
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:39,960
That kind. Blue in color.

65
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:58,640
Mr. He, I'll do it.

66
00:05:58,720 --> 00:06:00,200
What's on it?

67
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:04,280
Are you done? I'm about to suffocate.

68
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:10,560
I get it now. The trafficker
knocked the children out,

69
00:06:10,640 --> 00:06:12,160
then used the platform truck
to haul them out.

70
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:14,080
Search both directions.

71
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,680
See if there are any clues.

72
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:16,800
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN
GARAGE EXIT, NO ENTRY

73
00:06:16,880 --> 00:06:18,200
LASER ENGRAVING, CUSTOM GIFTS

74
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:19,880
There should've been a car outside
waiting to pick them up.

75
00:06:19,960 --> 00:06:22,120
It's not likely the person
dragged the platform truck around.

76
00:06:22,200 --> 00:06:23,920
Most likely that's what happened.

77
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,920
But there's still
a small chance otherwise.

78
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:30,680
Mr. Ran once told me
that out of 10,000 possibilities,

79
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:33,280
if you miss one, you might miss the truth.

80
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:36,720
Bai, Hui. You two take this side.
I'll check over there.

81
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:37,720
Okay.

82
00:06:44,880 --> 00:06:47,960
You can always count on Ran.

83
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:07,920
Captain Ran,

84
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,760
a case was transferred over
from Jiangwan Road Police Station.

85
00:07:09,840 --> 00:07:11,920
Last night, a woman
was attacked on the street.

86
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,200
She was hit in the back of the head
with a blunt object.

87
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:17,800
CRIME SCENE PHOTO

88
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:19,240
There were no witnesses at the scene,

89
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:21,080
and no clues were found either.

90
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:27,600
THIS WOMAN'S NAME IS ZHAO HONGMEI

91
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:50,880
The patient was struck in the head
with a blunt object,

92
00:07:50,960 --> 00:07:52,800
causing multiple brain bleeds.

93
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:56,400
Even if she survives,
the aftereffects will be severe.

94
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:59,600
In milder cases, she may be unable
to take care of herself.

95
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:02,160
In serious cases,
it could result in brain death.

96
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:03,640
That's the overall situation.

97
00:08:04,280 --> 00:08:05,760
Alright. Thank you.

98
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:13,360
Sir, does Zhao Hongmei's situation
remind you of anything?

99
00:08:18,360 --> 00:08:20,040
Can you tell me
what happened to your head first?

100
00:08:20,120 --> 00:08:21,720
Someone's trying to kill me.

101
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:25,000
He wanted to smash my head
in broad daylight.

102
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:27,360
You mean the same method?

103
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:31,240
The attacker who assaulted
Wu Shanlong is the same person?

104
00:08:35,039 --> 00:08:37,159
Zhao Hongmei and Wu Shanlong's
mutual social connections

105
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:39,120
are mainly linked to Hongyun Huihuang.

106
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:41,280
Wu Shanlong is the second-largest
shareholder there.

107
00:08:41,360 --> 00:08:42,880
Should we go check it out?

108
00:08:45,520 --> 00:08:47,000
What is it?

109
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:49,880
A lot of things line up now.

110
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:52,240
Wu Shanlong isn't smart.

111
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:54,280
But Zhao Hongmei is different.

112
00:08:56,440 --> 00:08:58,360
The money Zhao Hongmei used
to open Hongyun Huihuang

113
00:08:58,440 --> 00:08:59,880
was invested by Wu Shanlong.

114
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:00,960
So,

115
00:09:01,560 --> 00:09:05,560
it's very likely that she and Wu Shanlong
ganged up to scam Song Qingsong.

116
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:09,480
Do you think it's possible
that Song Qingsong's back?

117
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:13,880
A wanted fugitive would only risk
coming back to the country

118
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:16,360
for a serious reason.

119
00:09:16,880 --> 00:09:18,800
Most likely, he came back for revenge.

120
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:22,000
Any clues at the scene
where Zhao Hongmei was attacked?

121
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:25,800
I checked the photos taken by the station.
Nothing turned up.

122
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:34,440
No clues from Zhao Hongmei's side,

123
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:36,200
but there's something
on Wu Shanlong's end.

124
00:09:37,560 --> 00:09:38,760
Wu Shanlong?

125
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:42,320
WEIYANG PUBLIC SECURITY BUREAU
NANSHAN BRANCH WEINAN POLICE STATION

126
00:09:46,280 --> 00:09:47,640
Officer Ran. Careful, it's hot.

127
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:48,920
Thank you.

128
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:51,480
- You don't have to do that.
- Officer He, have some tea.

129
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:56,800
Officer He, it's been a while.

130
00:09:56,880 --> 00:09:57,840
You've put on some weight.

131
00:09:57,920 --> 00:09:58,920
JUSTICE FOR UNPAID WAGES
DUTIFUL AND RIGHTEOUS

132
00:09:59,000 --> 00:09:59,880
Happy weight.

133
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:02,800
Officer He, Officer Ran.

134
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:05,480
This is the evidence Wu Shanlong
brought in when he filed the report.

135
00:10:09,240 --> 00:10:10,400
PROPERTY OF EVIDENCE

136
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:23,480
WEIYANG BUS STATION

137
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:25,600
WEIYANG BUS GROUP

138
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:39,680
Never seen it. We don't
have wrenches like that here.

139
00:10:39,760 --> 00:10:41,120
SKILLED AND TRUE, FAST AND FAIR

140
00:10:44,040 --> 00:10:45,240
Thank you.

141
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:53,200
Excuse me.

142
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:54,720
Please take a look.

143
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:56,360
Have you seen a wrench like this before?

144
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:04,520
WEIYANG BUS STATION

145
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:07,120
Isn't this the tool
the unit used to issue to everyone

146
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,760
when we first started working?

147
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:12,120
You're right.

148
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:14,600
A couple of years ago,
the fleet was merged into the company.

149
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:16,600
That whole batch of tools
was phased out at once.

150
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:18,680
Where did they end up?

151
00:11:18,760 --> 00:11:22,040
RECYCLE

152
00:11:24,360 --> 00:11:26,360
Excuse me. Is your boss in?

153
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:28,440
- Inside.
- Thank you.

154
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:33,600
This should be the place.

155
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:38,720
Excuse me, sir.
I need to ask you something.

156
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:42,120
Have you seen this wrench before?

157
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:44,000
No.

158
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:51,320
- Have you seen this person?
- No.

159
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:57,760
POLICE RAN FANGXU

160
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:01,680
I'm a law-abiding citizen.

161
00:12:01,760 --> 00:12:03,600
Everything I do is above board.

162
00:12:09,240 --> 00:12:11,360
Above board, eh?

163
00:12:12,400 --> 00:12:14,680
Above board.

164
00:12:31,680 --> 00:12:32,840
Above board.

165
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:35,520
IRON CASTING

166
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:38,560
Officer, I honestly
have no idea about this.

167
00:12:38,640 --> 00:12:41,120
It must've been one of my workers
who bought it without thinking.

168
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:43,320
I'll contact the city management team
right away and return it to the owner.

169
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:48,320
Do you recognize this man now?

170
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:51,400
Looks a bit like the one
from the cement factory.

171
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:52,960
Song Qingsong.

172
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:56,440
But too many people come and go here.

173
00:12:56,520 --> 00:12:58,920
After all this time,
I really can't remember.

174
00:13:00,520 --> 00:13:01,640
Over here!

175
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:02,800
Sir!

176
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:05,160
Sir!

177
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:06,800
Help!

178
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:09,320
Ran! What happened?

179
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:11,080
Pull me up!

180
00:13:11,160 --> 00:13:13,560
Ran, what were you doing up there?

181
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:16,760
- What happened?
- Sir!

182
00:13:16,840 --> 00:13:17,960
Pull me up!

183
00:13:18,040 --> 00:13:19,160
How did this happen?

184
00:13:22,160 --> 00:13:24,520
- Why did you climb up here?
- I got stuck.

185
00:13:25,880 --> 00:13:26,880
That's dangerous.

186
00:13:27,960 --> 00:13:29,400
I got stuck right here.

187
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:36,440
Are you alright?

188
00:13:38,280 --> 00:13:40,040
What are you holding?

189
00:13:42,160 --> 00:13:43,560
Here.

190
00:13:44,080 --> 00:13:45,800
- What is this?
- Look here.

191
00:13:48,120 --> 00:13:49,560
QINGSONG CEMENT

192
00:14:27,040 --> 00:14:28,000
What's wrong?

193
00:14:28,680 --> 00:14:30,320
Missing Ran?

194
00:14:35,160 --> 00:14:37,080
There are so many people in the force,

195
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:39,360
but he's still the one
everyone respects most.

196
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:44,800
If he were here, this case
would've been solved by now.

197
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:51,760
He's not all-knowing.

198
00:14:51,840 --> 00:14:56,480
He made mistakes on his first case too
and failed as well.

199
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:02,040
Hopefully, my first case…

200
00:15:02,760 --> 00:15:05,400
<i>Mr. He, we found a syringe</i>
<i>by the roadside.</i>

201
00:15:24,280 --> 00:15:26,360
Han Zi'ang had two needle marks
on his arm.

202
00:15:27,800 --> 00:15:31,240
Could it be he was drugged
in the internet café and dragged out,

203
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:33,000
then woke up from the bumps
while on the platform truck?

204
00:15:33,080 --> 00:15:35,040
So the trafficker gave him another shot.

205
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:37,480
But he kept struggling,

206
00:15:37,560 --> 00:15:39,880
and the syringe
got knocked loose and fell here.

207
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:42,400
The trafficker was afraid
he would cry for help,

208
00:15:42,480 --> 00:15:43,640
so they knocked him out.

209
00:15:43,720 --> 00:15:45,680
That's how Han Zi'ang
got the injury on his head.

210
00:15:46,720 --> 00:15:49,400
But Han Zi'ang was found
inside New York Block.

211
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:50,600
How do we explain that?

212
00:15:51,920 --> 00:15:53,880
Why would the trafficker
use a platform truck

213
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:55,560
to drag him that far?

214
00:15:57,760 --> 00:16:01,160
Because the underground garage has stairs
leading to B1 of New York Block.

215
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:02,480
The platform truck couldn't go up.

216
00:16:16,360 --> 00:16:18,440
This road goes straight
to the main gate of Yuanlongli.

217
00:16:18,960 --> 00:16:21,920
Han Zi'ang was brought back
into Yuanlongli.

218
00:16:26,040 --> 00:16:29,720
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

219
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:41,120
No need to ask.
Those cameras broke long ago.

220
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:17,200
On the day Han Zi'ang injured a man,

221
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:19,359
no one pulling a platform truck was seen.

222
00:17:22,119 --> 00:17:23,359
Check the day before.

223
00:17:34,080 --> 00:17:35,040
Hold on.

224
00:17:36,080 --> 00:17:38,080
This person is a resident here.

225
00:17:39,040 --> 00:17:40,280
Wearing a cap.

226
00:17:40,360 --> 00:17:41,360
Can't see the face clearly.

227
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:54,800
Mister.

228
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:55,720
POLICE

229
00:17:55,800 --> 00:17:57,880
Your wound is serious.
Come with me and get it treated, alright?

230
00:17:58,920 --> 00:18:00,440
Can you hear me?

231
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:02,000
Mister?

232
00:19:41,920 --> 00:19:43,000
Wait.

233
00:19:43,840 --> 00:19:47,920
The layout for No. 16
should have another room.

234
00:20:16,640 --> 00:20:17,720
Careful!

235
00:20:19,560 --> 00:20:21,280
They're a bit triggered right now.

236
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:27,320
Hush.

237
00:20:31,760 --> 00:20:33,160
Ponies,

238
00:20:33,760 --> 00:20:35,000
Dad is home.

239
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:54,760
POLICE

240
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:57,800
How are things?

241
00:20:57,880 --> 00:20:59,120
Initial diagnosis says they're fine.

242
00:20:59,200 --> 00:21:00,360
We'll take them to the hospital now.

243
00:21:00,440 --> 00:21:01,560
Alright.

244
00:21:04,640 --> 00:21:05,480
Get him in the car.

245
00:21:10,080 --> 00:21:11,040
Captain Qu.

246
00:21:11,120 --> 00:21:12,680
- Captain Qu.
- Bai, Hui.

247
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:15,240
You two did a great job.

248
00:21:15,840 --> 00:21:16,680
No.

249
00:21:16,760 --> 00:21:18,440
- We were just backing them up.
- Right.

250
00:21:18,520 --> 00:21:21,360
The credit should go to Mr. He, Xiaohe
and Zhong who were guiding us.

251
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:23,880
The real credit goes to you young people.

252
00:21:24,680 --> 00:21:27,880
Old folks shouldn't be stuck in old ways.

253
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:29,880
We should trust the younger generation

254
00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:32,200
and give them a chance to shine.

255
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:35,400
Back then, Ran was just a fresh graduate.

256
00:21:35,480 --> 00:21:38,480
As his mentor, I gave him
full trust and support.

257
00:21:39,080 --> 00:21:40,040
You've got that backward, haven't you?

258
00:21:40,120 --> 00:21:42,200
Who was supporting whom?

259
00:21:42,280 --> 00:21:43,480
Qu Dahai,

260
00:21:44,120 --> 00:21:46,920
forget everyone else, just between us two,

261
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:50,600
who's better at cracking big cases
is pretty obvious, right?

262
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:54,000
Isn't everything you know
learned from Captain Ran?

263
00:21:56,080 --> 00:21:57,600
Come on. I'm treating you all
to some good food.

264
00:21:57,680 --> 00:21:59,640
- Alright.
- Thank you, Mr. He.

265
00:22:44,440 --> 00:22:48,200
CAROUSEL'S DEAD HEAT

266
00:23:51,880 --> 00:23:52,920
<i>Keyboard,</i>

267
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:58,040
<i>you're surely going to become</i>
<i>the best keyboard player.</i>

268
00:24:24,040 --> 00:24:25,160
Peng Dachuang.

269
00:24:25,760 --> 00:24:27,240
The facts are clear,

270
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:30,240
and the chain of evidence
is complete. I advise you…

271
00:24:30,320 --> 00:24:31,960
Can I have a cigarette?

272
00:24:45,920 --> 00:24:49,800
- I advise you…
- You attacked police officers.

273
00:24:49,880 --> 00:24:51,920
- That adds another charge.
- Behave yourself.

274
00:24:56,240 --> 00:24:57,120
Are you alright?

275
00:25:02,520 --> 00:25:03,560
Captain Qu.

276
00:25:07,720 --> 00:25:09,120
Get your wound treated.

277
00:25:10,920 --> 00:25:12,640
- What is it?
- Captain Qu,

278
00:25:12,720 --> 00:25:13,920
can I try?

279
00:25:15,680 --> 00:25:16,520
Have you interrogated a suspect before?

280
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:19,800
No.

281
00:25:19,880 --> 00:25:22,320
But I'm good friends
with Peng Dachuang's son.

282
00:25:30,240 --> 00:25:31,560
You have half an hour.

283
00:25:36,720 --> 00:25:37,960
We'll be waiting next door.

284
00:25:38,040 --> 00:25:39,640
If anything happens, wave to us.

285
00:25:40,480 --> 00:25:41,320
Okay.

286
00:25:54,160 --> 00:25:55,360
- Get lost!
- I'm here.

287
00:25:55,440 --> 00:25:56,520
I'm here.

288
00:25:57,720 --> 00:25:58,960
Why are you so slow with homework?

289
00:25:59,040 --> 00:26:00,480
We already came up with hundreds of names.

290
00:26:00,560 --> 00:26:03,080
I thought of one.
Let's call it Carousel Band.

291
00:26:03,160 --> 00:26:04,320
Isn't it cool?

292
00:26:05,080 --> 00:26:06,960
Are you advertising your dad's bar?

293
00:26:07,040 --> 00:26:10,880
Everyone knows your dad's bar
is called Carousel's Dead Heat.

294
00:26:10,960 --> 00:26:13,640
Then do you know
why my dad's bar is called Carousel?

295
00:26:14,680 --> 00:26:17,200
Because my nickname is Pony.

296
00:26:17,280 --> 00:26:20,480
My dad named the bar that
because he knew I loved carousels.

297
00:26:20,560 --> 00:26:23,200
I don't believe it. He's so harsh on you.

298
00:26:23,280 --> 00:26:24,480
Pony?

299
00:26:25,320 --> 00:26:26,600
Pony?

300
00:26:26,680 --> 00:26:27,880
Pony…

301
00:27:11,560 --> 00:27:15,000
Peng Dachuang, why did you kidnap
those children?

302
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:25,560
<i>Was it because of…</i>

303
00:27:26,440 --> 00:27:27,280
Pony?

304
00:27:28,040 --> 00:27:29,160
CAROUSEL'S DEAD HEAT

305
00:27:58,080 --> 00:27:59,520
Pony…

306
00:28:01,400 --> 00:28:03,200
Pony…

307
00:28:06,920 --> 00:28:09,040
My Pony…

308
00:28:09,960 --> 00:28:12,480
Pony…

309
00:28:15,120 --> 00:28:17,520
The ambulance is here! Make way! Hurry!

310
00:28:17,600 --> 00:28:18,920
What happened?

311
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:20,360
What happened here?

312
00:28:21,640 --> 00:28:23,760
- Sir, step back.
- Back up a little.

313
00:28:23,840 --> 00:28:26,200
- Sir. Sir.
- Sir.

314
00:28:26,280 --> 00:28:28,680
Get lost!

315
00:28:28,760 --> 00:28:30,640
Get lost!

316
00:28:32,160 --> 00:28:35,120
Pony…

317
00:28:36,600 --> 00:28:37,720
Mr. Peng,

318
00:28:38,800 --> 00:28:41,800
the girl next to Pony in this photo is me.

319
00:28:44,200 --> 00:28:46,480
Pony was my best friend.

320
00:28:46,560 --> 00:28:49,080
I understand your pain.

321
00:28:49,160 --> 00:28:51,240
I'm sorry that he died.

322
00:28:51,320 --> 00:28:53,720
Who told you he's dead?
Who told you he's dead?

323
00:28:53,800 --> 00:28:55,680
I see him every day.

324
00:28:55,760 --> 00:28:57,480
I see him every day.

325
00:28:57,560 --> 00:29:01,360
- Dad, I'm hiding now.
- I'm coming to catch you.

326
00:29:05,440 --> 00:29:06,520
Pony,

327
00:29:06,600 --> 00:29:08,360
- found you.
- Dad!

328
00:29:08,440 --> 00:29:09,680
What are you doing?

329
00:29:13,920 --> 00:29:16,800
Those ponies are naughty.
They never want to come home.

330
00:29:30,680 --> 00:29:33,920
Later… Later, they told me

331
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:36,640
Yuanlongli was going to be demolished
and told me to move out.

332
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:46,960
DEMOLITION

333
00:29:48,040 --> 00:29:49,520
<i>If I moved away,</i>

334
00:29:50,640 --> 00:29:52,160
<i>how would Pony find his way home?</i>

335
00:30:32,960 --> 00:30:34,080
Who are you looking for?

336
00:30:37,680 --> 00:30:39,520
Is someone in your house beating a child?

337
00:30:40,120 --> 00:30:41,200
There's no child in my house.

338
00:30:45,520 --> 00:30:46,440
What are you up to?

339
00:30:47,200 --> 00:30:48,200
It's in your house.

340
00:30:50,400 --> 00:30:52,480
Are you insane?

341
00:30:54,840 --> 00:30:56,240
Get out of here.

342
00:30:56,840 --> 00:30:58,800
I'm calling the police. Leave now.

343
00:31:05,840 --> 00:31:07,240
Move aside!

344
00:31:14,280 --> 00:31:17,280
Please. Please. Please.

345
00:31:17,360 --> 00:31:18,560
It's not what you think.

346
00:31:18,640 --> 00:31:20,360
I'll send him home right now.

347
00:31:20,440 --> 00:31:22,080
As if I'd believe you.

348
00:31:22,160 --> 00:31:23,560
You're a trafficker.

349
00:31:23,640 --> 00:31:24,880
Weren't you going to call the police?

350
00:31:24,960 --> 00:31:26,800
Fine. I'll call right now.

351
00:31:26,880 --> 00:31:28,400
Please. Don't call the police.

352
00:31:28,480 --> 00:31:29,240
- Get off.
- Don't call the police.

353
00:31:32,440 --> 00:31:33,840
Boy, don't be scared.

354
00:31:33,920 --> 00:31:34,880
I'll get you out of here.

355
00:31:35,560 --> 00:31:38,240
Don't be scared.
I'll take you home right now.

356
00:31:40,800 --> 00:31:42,200
Don't be scared.

357
00:32:08,040 --> 00:32:10,440
Help! Help!

358
00:32:10,520 --> 00:32:12,080
Help!

359
00:32:12,680 --> 00:32:14,560
Help… Help…

360
00:32:56,160 --> 00:32:57,280
Hang in there.

361
00:32:58,440 --> 00:32:59,640
I know it hurts.

362
00:32:59,720 --> 00:33:00,800
Hang in there.

363
00:33:04,760 --> 00:33:07,320
Come. Let me untie the rope for you.

364
00:33:12,120 --> 00:33:13,400
Does it hurt?

365
00:33:15,720 --> 00:33:17,080
Human traffickers deserve to die.

366
00:33:17,160 --> 00:33:18,000
They deserve to die.

367
00:33:18,080 --> 00:33:20,200
They all deserve to die.
They all deserve to die.

368
00:33:20,280 --> 00:33:24,000
Why did that boy
go to your house afterward?

369
00:33:35,760 --> 00:33:37,680
Pony told me

370
00:33:38,760 --> 00:33:41,200
his parents fought every day.

371
00:33:42,480 --> 00:33:43,800
He didn't want to go home.

372
00:33:45,200 --> 00:33:48,040
QINGSONG CEMENT FACTORY, WEIYANG CITY

373
00:34:05,200 --> 00:34:07,440
CEMENT FACTORY
PAY UP, DEBT MUST BE PAID

374
00:34:07,520 --> 00:34:08,480
Do you have a saw in your car?

375
00:34:18,360 --> 00:34:24,639
QINGSONG CEMENT FACTORY, WEIYANG CITY

376
00:34:26,120 --> 00:34:27,239
Can you do this?

377
00:34:27,320 --> 00:34:30,040
- If not, come down.
- I'm fine.

378
00:34:31,880 --> 00:34:33,480
Sir. Over here.

379
00:34:35,199 --> 00:34:36,560
What's going on?

380
00:34:37,639 --> 00:34:38,960
I can't free up a hand.

381
00:34:43,400 --> 00:34:44,639
Hold the bag for me.

382
00:34:53,480 --> 00:34:54,520
Let's split up and search.

383
00:34:54,600 --> 00:34:56,239
- You go that side. I'll go this side.
- Alright.

384
00:36:00,360 --> 00:36:01,200
How is it?

385
00:36:02,360 --> 00:36:04,240
- Nothing on my side.
- Same here.

386
00:36:06,320 --> 00:36:07,720
Let's check over there.

387
00:36:09,880 --> 00:36:11,080
Wait.

388
00:36:15,720 --> 00:36:18,320
QINGSONG CEMENT

389
00:36:18,400 --> 00:36:20,120
Why is smoke coming from up there?

390
00:36:22,840 --> 00:36:23,840
Let's go check it out.

391
00:36:25,320 --> 00:36:26,560
Careful, sir.

392
00:36:28,120 --> 00:36:29,800
Slow down.

393
00:36:31,160 --> 00:36:32,920
- Sir.
- It's pitch black.

394
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:35,760
Climbing stairs is good
for your three highs.

395
00:36:35,840 --> 00:36:37,000
As if.

396
00:36:37,560 --> 00:36:38,920
Slow down.

397
00:36:40,720 --> 00:36:42,880
Climbing stairs helps lose belly fat.

398
00:36:43,400 --> 00:36:45,320
I have no belly fat.

399
00:36:45,400 --> 00:36:47,760
When I was young,
my waist was slimmer than yours.

400
00:37:06,120 --> 00:37:07,760
Sir.

401
00:37:31,800 --> 00:37:32,840
Song Qingsong.

402
00:37:36,400 --> 00:37:37,920
Long time no see, officers.

403
00:37:39,240 --> 00:37:41,320
Why are you back in Weiyang?

404
00:37:49,520 --> 00:37:51,680
Have a seat. Let's sit and talk.

405
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:56,200
I haven't met anyone since I've been here.

406
00:38:00,240 --> 00:38:02,240
You want to ask about
Xu Meng and her father, right?

407
00:38:02,320 --> 00:38:04,560
And Wu Shanlong and Zhao Hongmei.

408
00:38:06,720 --> 00:38:07,680
Let's do it one by one.

409
00:38:09,200 --> 00:38:11,440
About that young woman
at the foot massage shop,

410
00:38:12,040 --> 00:38:14,160
it's true I paid Wu Shanlong
to get rid of her.

411
00:38:16,520 --> 00:38:18,280
Back then, Wu Shanlong told me

412
00:38:18,360 --> 00:38:21,160
Cripple Du had someone
snatch the body away.

413
00:38:22,360 --> 00:38:26,440
That scoundrel knew
Cripple Du and me were enemies.

414
00:38:27,040 --> 00:38:28,640
But the world is small.

415
00:38:29,160 --> 00:38:31,320
I ran into him when I was overseas.

416
00:38:32,200 --> 00:38:33,920
He had fled too.

417
00:38:37,360 --> 00:38:39,440
Where is Xu Meng's body?

418
00:38:41,280 --> 00:38:43,840
Wu Shanlong was a coward.

419
00:38:44,440 --> 00:38:46,560
He took photos.
He definitely destroyed them.

420
00:38:47,720 --> 00:38:50,080
Why did you go after Zhao Hongmei?

421
00:38:51,560 --> 00:38:53,000
That wretched woman

422
00:38:53,080 --> 00:38:55,680
ganged up with Wu Shanlong
and swindled me out of my money.

423
00:38:55,760 --> 00:38:58,720
I worked half my life
to build that factory.

424
00:38:58,800 --> 00:39:00,360
The pair of them ruined it.

425
00:39:00,440 --> 00:39:02,440
On top of that, they owed
the workers a lot of money.

426
00:39:02,520 --> 00:39:04,720
Those who had followed me
for over 20 years

427
00:39:04,800 --> 00:39:06,960
couldn't even afford medical treatment.

428
00:39:09,760 --> 00:39:12,000
That's why you assaulted Wu Shanlong too?

429
00:39:13,080 --> 00:39:14,720
What I regret most is going soft

430
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:19,120
and not killing him.

431
00:39:47,000 --> 00:39:48,040
Song,

432
00:39:49,800 --> 00:39:51,920
life hasn't been easy for you
these past years, has it?

433
00:39:56,640 --> 00:39:58,480
When I first ran off,

434
00:39:59,360 --> 00:40:02,640
I thought about bringing
my wife and child over.

435
00:40:03,160 --> 00:40:04,960
But I couldn't reach them at all.

436
00:40:05,720 --> 00:40:07,240
Later, I found out

437
00:40:07,760 --> 00:40:11,560
that woman had already sold the house
and run off with my child.

438
00:40:19,160 --> 00:40:20,640
The money I took with me

439
00:40:21,800 --> 00:40:23,360
was gone in less than two years.

440
00:40:24,640 --> 00:40:27,440
I couldn't speak their language,
and I was undocumented.

441
00:40:28,320 --> 00:40:30,440
I could only do construction work
and make very little money.

442
00:40:33,280 --> 00:40:34,880
You would never guess it.

443
00:40:35,400 --> 00:40:36,400
In the end,

444
00:40:37,160 --> 00:40:39,280
it was Cripple Du who gave me money,

445
00:40:39,800 --> 00:40:42,120
so I could sneak back here
and get my revenge.

446
00:40:48,400 --> 00:40:52,000
We had been enemies half our lives,
but he actually gave me money.

447
00:40:54,880 --> 00:40:56,120
As for what I owed the workers,

448
00:40:57,080 --> 00:40:59,760
I sold components from the factory
to pay them back.

449
00:41:00,600 --> 00:41:03,240
Now my revenge is done.
I don't care about anything anymore.

450
00:41:04,400 --> 00:41:07,480
I admit everything I did.

451
00:41:08,920 --> 00:41:09,960
Come on.

452
00:41:22,000 --> 00:41:22,920
We'll do that after we go downstairs.

453
00:41:25,200 --> 00:41:26,600
Give me a moment to tidy up.

454
00:41:49,360 --> 00:41:50,360
Thank you.
